In the United States, the individual disc of ''The Fame Monster'' charted at number five on the [[Billboard_200|''Billboard'' 200]] with sales of 174,000 copies while the double disc deluxe edition, including the original ''The Fame'', moved up from number 34 to number 6 with sales of 151,000 copies.<ref name="bb200">{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/266540/susan-boyle-sees-dream-soar-to-no-1-on-billboard-200|title=Susan Boyle Sees Dream Soar To No. 1 On Billboard 200|date=2009-12-02|accessdate=2009-12-03|work=Billboard|last=Pietrolungo|first=Silvio|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130414024904/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/266540/susan-boyle-sees-dream-soar-to-no-1-on-billboard-200|archivedate=2013-04-14}}</ref> The album also topped the [[Digital_Albums|Digital Albums]] chart with sales of 65,000. Seven of the eight songs from the record also charted on the [[Hot_Digital_Songs|Hot Digital Songs]] chart, led by "Bad Romance" which held the top position for the second week with sales of 218,000 copies. In total Gaga had 11 songs that week charting on the Digital Songs.<ref name="women take charge">{{Cite news|url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart_watch/42389/week-ending-nov-29-2009-women-take-charge/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111013084124/http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart_watch/42389/week-ending-nov-29-2009-women-take-charge/|archivedate=2011-10-13|title=Week Ending Nov. 29, 2009: Women Take Charge|last=Grein|first=Paul|date=2009-12-02|publisher=Yahoo!|accessdate=2009-12-03}}</ref> ''The Fame Monster'' topped the [[Dance/Electronic_Albums|Dance/Electronic Albums]] chart, replacing ''The Fame'' and becoming Gaga's second number one album on the chart.<ref name="dancee">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/dance-electronic-albums/2009-12-12|title=Billboard Dance/Electronic Albums: Week of December 12, 2009|work=Billboard|accessdate=2009-12-04|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107141324/http://www.billboard.com/charts/dance-electronic-albums/2009-12-12|archivedate=2016-11-07}}</ref>

In January 2010, the album was certified [[RIAA_certifications|platinum]] by the [[Recording_Industry_Association_of_America|Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) for shipment of a million copies.<ref name="riaa" /> As of February 2018, ''The Fame Monster'' has sold 1.64 million copies in the United States, according to [[Nielsen_Soundscan|Nielsen Soundscan]].<ref name="uscareersales18">{{cite magazine|title=Ask Billboard: Lady Gaga's Career Sales, The Biggest No. 2 Hits & Ed Sheeran's Latest Chart Record|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8218920/-lady-gaga-sales-number-2-hot-100-hits-ed-sheeran-record-ask-billboard|date=2018-02-25|accessdate=2018-02-25|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary}}</ref> For the 2010 ''Billboard'' year end tabulation, ''The Fame Monster'' was ranked at number 13 on the ''Billboard'' 200 and number two on the Dance/Electronic Albums chart.<ref name="Billboard 200"/><ref name="Billboard dance"/> In Canada, the album debuted and peaked at number six on the ''Billboard'' [[Canadian_Albums_Chart|Canadian Albums Chart]].<ref name="canadian">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/canadian-albums/2009-12-19|title=Canadian Albums Chart: Week Ending December 19, 2009|date=2010-01-30|accessdate=2010-11-03|work=Billboard|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129041631/http://www.billboard.com/charts/canadian-albums/2009-12-19|archivedate=2016-01-29}}</ref> It was the 23rd best selling album in the country for 2010.<ref name="Canadian Chart"/>

In Australia, ''The Fame Monster'' initially charted with ''The Fame'', but was later considered as a standalone entry. It debuted at number 6 on the ARIA Albums Chart and in its 18th week, the record climbed to number one.<ref name="aus"/> It received a triple platinum certification by the [[Australian_Recording_Industry_Association|Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA) for shipments of 210,000 copies of the album.<ref name="ariacerti"/> In Japan, after being present on the [[Oricon|Oricon]] Albums Chart for over 20 weeks, the album reached its peak position of number two in May 2010.<ref name="jap"/> By July 2011, the album had sold 548,000 copies in Japan and ranked at number 14 on the year end list for 2010.<ref name="japsales">{{cite news|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/88250/full/|script-title=ja:【オリコン】ガガ、アヴリル以来2作連続50万枚突破　11年海外歌手暫定首位|language=ja|publisher=[[Oricon|Oricon]]|date=2011-07-26|accessdate=2011-07-26|trans-title=Lady Gaga, first place in Japan debut in 2 years|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140118152911/http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/88250/full/|archivedate=2014-01-18}}</ref><ref name="oriconyy"/>

In the United Kingdom, ''The Fame Monster'' was only available as a deluxe edition, not as a stand-alone album, hence it charted as part of ''The Fame''. In its debut week, the record moved from number 55 to number 7 on the [[UK_Albums_Chart|UK Albums Chart]].<ref name="uk" /> All the new tracks from ''The Fame Monster'' charted within the top 200 of the [[UK_Singles_Chart|UK Singles Chart]].<ref>{{cite journal|title=The Official UK Singles Chart for the week ending December 5, 2009|journal=[[UKChartsPlus|UKChartsPlus]]|issue=432|page=3|publisher=IQ Ware Ltd|location=Milton Keynes}}</ref> On the week ending March 6, 2010, ''The Fame'' reached the top of the chart.<ref name="uk"/> ''The Fame Monster'' also charted with ''The Fame'' in Denmark, Ireland and Germany; it reached the top of the charts in the last two territories.<ref name="fla"/><ref name="ger"/> Due to its chart activity across the European markets, ''The Fame Monster'' peaked at number 13 on the [[European_Top_100_Albums|European Top 100 Albums]] chart.<ref name="european">{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/959498/keha-lady-gaga-rule-euro-charts|title=Ke$ha, Lady Gaga Rule Euro Charts|last=Sexton|first=Paul|date=2010-02-04|work=Billboard|accessdate=2010-02-05|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141008040100/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/959498/keha-lady-gaga-rule-euro-charts|archivedate=2014-10-08}}</ref> It was certified triple platinum by the [[International_Federation_of_the_Phonographic_Industry|International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]] (IFPI) for shipment of three million copies across the continent.<ref name="ifpieuro" />
